 First, we need to calculate the total amount Peter will spend on the movie tickets and popcorn. Since he gets a ticket for $7 and popcorn for $7, the total cost per visit is $14. With 42 dollars available for the week, we divide this amount by the cost per visit to find out how many times Peter can go to the movies
 \text{Number of visits} = \frac{\text{Total budget}}{\text{Cost per visit}} 
 \text{Number of visits} = \frac{42}{14} 
