 \text{Total jellyfish} = 5 \text{ springs} \times 4 \text{ jellyfish/spring/hour} 
 \text{Total jellyfish} = 20 \text{ jellyfish} 

Therefore, 5 springs working at the same rate would create 20 jellyfish in 4 hours.
The answer is: 20

