Next, we calculate the time it would take him to speak 10 pages. We know each page has 450 words per page. To find the total number of words in 10 pages, we multiply the number of pages by the number of words per page.
 \text{Total Words} = 10 \text{ pages} \times 450 \text{ words/page} 
 \text{Total Words} = 4500 \text{ words} 
Now, we divide the total words by the new speed to find the time it takes.
 \text{Time} = \frac{\text{Total Words}}{\text{New Speed}} 
 \text{Time} = \frac{4500}{375} 
 \text{Time} = 12 \text{ minutes} 
Therefore, it would take John 12 minutes to speak 10 pages.
The answer is: 12 minutes

